28]]'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Republican}}|'''74.8%''' ''2,861''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Democratic}}|24.8% ''950''\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:honeyDew;\"|0.4% ''15''\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Republican}}|'''[[1924 United States presidential election|1924]]'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Republican}}|'''69.6%''' ''2,750''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Democratic}}|26.5% ''1,047''\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:honeyDew;\"|3.9% ''155''\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Republican}}|'''[[1920 United States presidential election|1920]]'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Republican}}|'''79.2%''' ''3,002''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Democratic}}|19.6% ''742''\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:honeyDew;\"|1.2% ''46''\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Republican}}|'''[[1916 United States presidential election in Illinois|1916]]'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Republican}}|'''65.4%''' ''2,885''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Democratic}}|31.5% ''1,389''\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:honeyDew;\"|3.1% ''138''\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Progressive}}|'''[[1912 United States presidential election in Illinois|1912]]'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Republican}}|34.0% ''817''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Democratic}}|27.0% ''650''\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:honeyDew;\"|'''38.9%''' ''936''{{efn|There were only 818 votes for the leading \u201cother\u201d candidate, [[Progressive Party (United States, 1912)|Progressive]] [[Theodore Roosevelt]], plus 100 for the [[Prohibition Party]]\u2019s [[Eugene Chafin]], 16 for Socialist [[Eugene Debs]], and 3 for [[Socialist Labor Party of America|Socialist Labor]] candidate [[Arthur E. Reimer|Arthur Reimer]]